reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Amazing for electronics/storage!
reviews.reviewText: I have only had this organizer for a couple of days now, but everything that I could possibly need on a daily basis I've moved into this. Overall I think it has an okay build quality, the only thing I don't completely like about it is that the mesh pouches inside have elastic on them that looks like they'd definitely stretch out over time. They have their use cases, however if I wanted to put AirPods or something of similar size into them, they bulge pretty bad and I can see how it can cause problems over time with the durability. It's not super big, so if you're looking for something that's going to be able to hold EVERYTHING (power banks, cables, earbuds, etc.) it's probably not going to work for you. However, with the size it is it ends up being a super convenient package and does what I need it to do perfectly!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great to organize my cords, but not as big as I expected
reviews.reviewText: I took this on an international trip because I had a lot of devices I needed to charge.It was great for all my various cords, but the pic is a little misleading.It shows that it is large enough for a portable power supply, but only if it is a smaller, slim box (think the size of a slim smartphone). My portable charger was a bigger capacity, so I had to store it separately. I never carried my iPhone 13 Pro in this case, but it would have fit. However, I was able to store and organize seven cords in this (phone, Apple Watch, longer lightening cable, and various other cords I needed) along with a small plug for my lightening cable, so it served its purpose.I will keep it to continue storing my various cables in my work bag.It is sturdy and the zippers are good. I think it will last a long time. I got the pink color, and the color is as pictured.

It's decent quality and the zippers seem like they would hold up but the compartments for cords are for little mini cords. I like long phone charging cables and the 6ft and 10ft ones do not fill well in the compartments at all.

CAOODKDK Electronics Accessories Organizer Pouch is alright for what it is. Could it be better? Yes, but only a little better. It's actually a pretty good little casde.I bought the two sided case in black for a couple reasons. One being that I was going to need both sides. The other being that all but one of the other colours were more expensive. Some were close to $10 more.On the up side, it's a neat little case with enough pockets on one side to store and organize most of the little cables you might need. There is also a long slim pocket that could hold a mobile phone or battery pack. Charge cables, head phones, and so on, will fit quite nicely into the pockets provided they are not too long. The flip side of the case has two larger pockets that will easily store a battery pack and an external hard drive.It's roughly the size of a pencil case and even fully load is not that heavy. The zippers on both pockets both work well. No snags or jams to speak of. The water resistant claim seems to hold up, but I don't think I'm going to test that repeatedly. All in all, it's good enough to be home base for most of the little things you might otherwise end up digging through your suitcase/carry-on for.I have packed 4 cables, a set of ear buds, 2 battery packs, a pouch of USB-C converters and a portable LED lamp with all of it's attachments. The case was pretty much at capacity after that.Now the negatives... My iPhone charger will not fit in the case, nor will one of the other (longer) charge cables I need to have with me. Also, one really has to watch how they pack the case, as it is soft shell all the way around. What you pack on one side impacts how much you can fit in the other. I'm impressed with how much the case will hold, but not being deep enough to hold the charger is a bit of a negative, as it is most likely to be the item I misplace or leave behind. It just looked a little bigger in the pictures I guess.
